
Install Google Chrome Stable on Ubuntu also works on Debian and Linux Mint.

Copy and paste each line in the terminal waiting for each process to finish first.

1. wget https://dl.google.com/linux/direct/google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb

2. sudo dpkg -i google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb

3. sudo apt-get -f install 

Enjoy your newly installed Web Browser.
